{
  "description": "PROPOSED roll-up formulas for the TELECOM (Mobily) master FS. Drafted by Claude FOR Sabahat/Abhishek review — NOT yet confirmed. Transcribed from Mobily's printed FY2024 subtotal structure. The runtime AI proposers never author these (they map leaf labels only); the engine computes them deterministically. IMPORTANT: this file and the seed's kind/components both come from the same Claude proposal, so the fidelity check between them is CIRCULAR and proves only seed==rollups, NOT correctness. Correctness comes from (a) a human reviewing every formula below against Mobily's published statement, and (b) the balance check actually balancing on real data.",
  "sign_convention": "Amounts use the TB's native sign: income positive, expenses/zakat/tax stored NEGATIVE. Subtotals therefore use '+' on an already-negative value (e.g. Gross profit = Revenue + Cost of revenue, where Cost of revenue is negative). This mirrors Mobily's published statement. If a real client TB stores expenses POSITIVE, the per-client mapping must record that and the signs flip — flag at confirm, do NOT silently assume.",
  "rules": {
    "kinds": "leaf=populated by mapped TB accounts; net=income-minus-expense face line; subtotal=intermediate roll-up; total=spine total (always renders).",
    "render": "spine totals always render; net/subtotal render iff >=1 component present; empty intermediates hide.",
    "derive_order": "topological — subtotals first, then totals that consume them; a total may reference another (Total assets = Total non-current + Total current; Total equity & liabilities = Total equity + Total liabilities).",
    "orphan_guard": "every populated non-memo leaf must appear in some coverage total's component closure.",
    "balance_check": "Total assets vs Total shareholders' equity and liabilities; mismatch -> non-blocking finding showing the difference, never auto-corrected."
  },
  "must_add_to_seed": [
    "tc_total_assets",
    "tc_total_equity",
    "tc_total_liabilities",
    "tc_total_oe",
    "tc_net_profit",
    "tc_total_ci"
  ],
